\section{Conclusion}
\subsection{}



\begin{frame}{Summary}
  \begin{minipage}[c][.65\textheight][c]{\linewidth}
    \begin{itemize}
      \setlength\itemsep{\fill}
      \item The phytobiome of woody plant roots is important and understudied.
      \item Rhododendrons are economically and aesthetically important for the Northwest.
      \item Metabarcoding allows for culture-independent analysis of phytobiomes.
      \item Clusters of similar sequences (OTUs) can function as species analogs. 
      \item Patterns in species abundance across samples with differing characteristics can reveal the driving factors behind community composition.
    \end{itemize} 
  \end{minipage}%
\end{frame}


